[Data by country, area, or territory for 26 Oct 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20OCT26_1635362066.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 5.0% of cases and 7.7% of deaths in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 92.93 million cases. The USA and Canada did not report any cases, while Brazil, Colombia, Chile, and Cuba reported over 1000 cases. An additional 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 74.0% of daily case numbers and 68.6% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 75.40 million cases. Some countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (5 cases), Sweden, and Switzerland (one case), among others; 27 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 4.8% of daily case numbers and 5.9% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 16.26 million cases. Iran (7516) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Jordan and Iraq. Egypt, Libya, and Pakistan reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Somalia and Sudan, among others, did not report any cases over the last 24 hours.

- The African region reported 1.3% of daily case numbers and 1.9% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 6.13 million cases. Botswana (1066) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Nigeria (876). Many countries, including Cameroon, Benin, Congo, and Sierra Leone, among others, did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 7.0% of daily case numbers and 6.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 9.28 million cases. Malaysia reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 4000 cases), followed by Philippines, Viet Nam, Singapore, Australia, South Korea, and Laos.

- The South East Asia region reported 4.8% of the daily newly reported cases and 5.9% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 43.83 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 12 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (7706), Myanmar (924), Indonesia (611), Nepal (569), and Bangladesh (276). Sri Lanka and Maldives did not report any cases over the last 24 hours.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 26 Oct 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

